It is IMPOSSIBLE. No matter how smart you are cracking IIT without studying is not a possibility because JEE does not only test your concepts but also how fast you can recollect and implement in the exam. So you may be a prodigy who knows everything but the fast speed and recollecting ability can only be learned through practice. Reservation of some kind like SC, ST, OBC, GIRLS, or any other quota may help you in cracking the exam with lesser efforts but efforts are needed. By chance if you crack IIT without studying you will regret getting in because things are going to be very tough for you because everything that will be taught assuming that your basics of JEE are clear. So when you see all the problems you will just regret getting into IIT the first place. So if you don't study pray that you don't get IIT because you will suffer once getting in.

Your question if in jest has been answered equally well by many but if your question was serious and it meant “not slogging for say 10hours” if that is what is studying then it is well possible if you are smart enough. One truth today is the bunch of guys getting into IIT seem to be more obsessed and possessed but not passionate or smart. Thanks to foolish coaching institutes. I can state that the quality of intake has suffered. So if you are serious, try to learn the fundamentals, don't try to do every shit problem that your suggested material (coaching institute or whatever) suggests. Instead try to learn whatever perfectly. Another truth is JEE Advanced does not have high cutoffs. So if you studied say 70% of the syllabus perfectly you can actually in the top. If you learnt even 50% of the syllabus perfectly then you will be in. A 40% score in JEE advanced should get you into some branch in a top 5 IIT. So perfection is more important than slogging. That is the best I can say. From 1970s till today the cutoff for top 5 IITs for the last engineering seat (leave MSc and Biotech) needs around 40%; so if you learnt 50% perfectly and can produce 80% of it right you will be in. SIMPLE…From an IITian of 80s!
